  "SubGoals": [],
  "Description": "The TestSystemActorHandler goal is designed to test the functionality of a system actor handler by utilizing caching to share state. It caches a value for 10 minutes, calls a trace handler on a specific channel, logs a message to the system channel, retrieves the cached trace log, and checks if the log contains a specific trace message. If the expected message is not found, it throws an error indicating the test has failed. If the test passes, it logs a success message.",
